The paper deals with semantic image segmentation using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new CNN architecture, DenseNets, which has shown excellent results on image classification tasks, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of post-processing modules, such as Conditional Random Fields, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of parameters in the model, which could be related to neural network optimization (cs.NE).
